This paper is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category as it deals with the effectiveness of recommender systems and the impact of fairness on users' satisfaction. It may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it explores the relationship between user behavior and recommendation algorithms. Additionally, it may be relevant to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category as it discusses the potential negative impact of unfair recommendations on social dynamics. The Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category may also be relevant as the study aims to improve user experience with recommender systems. Finally, the Cybersecurity (cs.CY) sub-category may be relevant as unfair recommendations can potentially lead to privacy and security issues.
